    "## Part 3: Efficient Reading Strategies\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.1 Windowed Reading\n",
    "\n",
    "COGs excel at windowed reading - accessing only specific spatial regions:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Spatial Windows:** Define rectangular areas of interest\n",
    "2. **Tile-Aligned Access:** Optimize reads to match internal tile structure\n",
    "3. **Multi-Resolution Reading:** Select appropriate overview level\n",
    "4. **Lazy Loading:** Read data only when needed\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3.2 Overview Level Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "Choosing the right overview level optimizes performance:\n",
    "- **Analysis Scale:** Match resolution to analysis requirements\n",
    "- **Memory Constraints:** Use overviews to fit data in available memory\n",
    "- **Processing Speed:** Lower resolution = faster processing\n",
    "- **Quality Trade-offs:** Balance speed vs. spatial detail"
   ]
